@node Introduction "Introduction"
@{fg shine}
            Speak To Me V3.00 - By: John White - Shareware (£2.50).
           ---------------------------------------------------------

@{fg text}
 Speak To Me (STM) V3.00 is a Speech program that allows you to use most, if
 not all, of the Amiga speech functions. It is meant as a replacement SAY
 program with Speech/Language program developers in mind.

 STM needs at least Operating System 39, the Narrator.Device (V39+) and
 the Translator.Library (V37+) to work. If you are going to use the LOAD
 and SAVE Config File options you will also need the ASL.Library (V39+).

@{fg shine}
 General Notes@{fg text}

 * White Edge/Black Box gadgets are all Number string gadgets, except for
   the Voice, Language Text and Phonetic Text gadgets which are Text string
   gadgets. If you enter a number that is out of range you will get the
   default value for that particular number string gadget.

   Note: You do not have to enter 3 numbers, for example, when you only need
         to enter 2 numbers (I.e you can enter 023 or simply 23). However.
         As my string update routine does not filter out leading zeros, when
         you first load STM or a Config file the numbers will appear as 023
         for example and not as 23. For now, I would stick to using 3 digits
         instead of 2 digits.

 * Black Edge/White Box items have a direct purpose. To show text. When you
   click on their associated Button gadgets they cycle through their partic-
   ular text items.

 * Most functions can use a Keyboard Key, aswell Mouse_Key/s, and are high-
   lighted with a Black character. Here is a list of those keyboard keys
   NOT highlighted with a Black character:

   F1-F3   (with/out Left-Shift)  -  Amplify Buttons

   F4-F6   (with/out Left-Shift)  -  Echo Buttons

   F7-F10  (with/out Left-Shift)  -  Audio Channel Values

@{fg shine}
