 The next section covers Diphthongs, which are vowel sounds that change
 while they are pronounced. The word Boil is a good example. You start by
 pronouncing the letter O as a long vowel but end by pronouncing the letter
 I as a short vowel. The Amiga phoneme for this diphthong is OY.


 Diphthong         Produced
