@node Update "Update Information"
@{fg shine}
 * MC68020 Assembly Code  - By converting STM V1.14 into Assembly code from
                            `Amiga E' code I was able to cut STMs size by
                            approximately 30k. I chose MC68020 code over
                            MC68000 code because of its better/faster
                            instructions, which means STM will only work on
                            OS3+ Amigas. Use STM V1.13 if you are using an
                            A600.

 * Better Strings         - STM now uses Intuition Strings with routines
                            that give each string its default value if an
                            incorrect value was entered for that string.

 * Smaller Window         - I put a couple of the old options onto the Menu.

 * Improved ASL Requester - You can now choose any drawername and filename.

                            AddPart() does not overwrite your original
                            buffer, if you keep using the same buffer, thus
                            you get a garbage buffer second time around, etc
                            I fixed this by allocating a new buffer each
                            time the ASL Requester is used and then make a
                            copy of the buffer's contents before
                            deallocating the buffer.

 * Editable Voice Names   - You can now edit the names of the ten voices.
@endnode
